---
description: Auth and financial data handling — load for anything touching login, roles, or payments
alwaysApply: false
---
- Passwords: bcrypt/argon2 hashed, never stored or logged in plaintext.
- JWT or session-based auth — either is fine, but be consistent, and store
  role in the token/session, re-verify role server-side on every request.
- Residents may submit a transaction / UTR ID for an invoice, but that alone
  never marks an invoice paid. Only society staff (admin/treasurer) verifying
  the submission — or marking paid offline — updates invoice status.
- Never trust client-side claims of payment success. Server-side verification
  (staff action) is required before status changes.
- Do not log full payment transaction refs in client-side analytics.
- Never expose other residents' contact/vehicle details across flats unless
  the requester is manager/admin/staff.
